{
  "texts": [
    "The first step in the CLEAR pipeline is identifying all clinical entities in the input clinical notes using a NER model.",
    "The output of this step is a list of unique clinical entities contained in the notes.",
    "We implemented the initial NER step using zero-shot NER with Flan-T5-XXL due to its specialized NER instruction tuning 67.",
    "Most clinical NER models are domain-specific and are highly dependent on the dataset they were fine-tuned on.",
    "To minimize these limitations, we chose Flan-T5, a domain-agnostic model, for NER."
  ]
}